@startuml
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE)
'
' Current-side runtime flow as implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL
' (Phase A steps 1-10 = PLAN; Phase B steps 11-16 = EXECUTE) and the
' extended templates::MDD_RENDER_SKILL. The skill body is the executable
' contract the agent follows.
'
' CHANGE (cycle 0021): the implemented skill no longer stops after writing
' artifacts. The plan phase ends by handing off to a new execution phase
' that manages auth, dry-runs, applies, provisions, migrates, and routes
' traffic — pausing only at irreversible steps and halting on first error.
'
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "PLAN phase, as implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL: reject non-azure-container-apps targets, read .mdd/models + ../atlas-ate-server read-only, STOP for a blocking clarification on ambiguity OR a GENERALIZED landmine, CONFIRM the IaC dialect (step 4) AND the deployment purpose (step 5), run the ACCESS-COMPLETENESS pass (step 6), write diagram.puml + runbook.md, generate secure-by-default IaC in the confirmed dialect (step 8), then HAND OFF to SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE.")
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "As implemented in templates::MDD_RENDER_SKILL: /mdd-render rasterizes every .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to its deterministic .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg mirror. Additive, non-gating.")
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE, "EXECUTE phase, as implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL steps 11-16: manage cloud auth (az login + select/verify subscription, stop on mismatch), validate the IaC and run a DRY-RUN (terraform plan / az what-if) showing the diff, then walk the runbook via Bash. Idempotent/reversible steps run autonomously; the executor BLOCKS only at irreversible steps — one APPLY gate covering infra apply + secret writes + the pre-traffic migration job — then deploys the new revision at 0% traffic and health-checks it. The GO-LIVE gate surfaces the full production billing multi-factor state and BLOCKS before routing live traffic; never auto-confirmed. Execution HALTS on the first failed step. Realizes USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE + USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE; constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-*.")
title /mdd-deploy plan, execute, and inspection (current)

actor "Operator" as Op
participant "/mdd-deploy\n(skill: plan + executor)" as Dep
participant ".mdd/models/\ncomponents + use-cases" as Models
participant "../atlas-ate-server\n(target repo, read-only)" as Target
database ".mdd/deploy/\nazure-container-apps/" as Store
participant "../atlas-ate-server/\ninfra/ (generated IaC)" as Infra
participant "Bash: az, terraform, docker" as CLI
participant "Azure subscription\n(LIVE)" as Az
participant "/mdd-render" as Render
database ".mdd/rendered/deploy/" as Rendered

== SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE (PLAN) ==
Op -> Dep : /mdd-deploy <deployment description>
alt target is not azure-container-apps
  Dep --> Op : not yet supported (v1 = azure-container-apps only); stop
else target is azure-container-apps
  Dep -> Models : read components + use-cases (the "what")
  Dep -> Target : read README, Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml,\n.env.example, src (READ-ONLY)
  opt ambiguity OR a GENERALIZED landmine (app-config, purpose, or access-path)
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING clarification; SURFACE the gap
    Op --> Dep : decision
  end
  group step 4 — MANDATORY dialect confirmation (USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING confirm: "generate <dialect> IaC?"
    Op --> Dep : confirmed dialect
  end
  group step 5 — MANDATORY deployment-purpose confirmation (USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE)
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING confirm purpose + SURFACE options
    Op --> Dep : confirmed purpose + choices
  end
  group step 6 — ACCESS-COMPLETENESS pass (USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK)
    Dep -> Dep : name READER + WRITER for every secured store
    opt read-but-never-written, OR a writer with no admitted path
      Dep -> Op : BLOCKING: SURFACE the hole + connectivity options
      Op --> Dep : choice
    end
  end
  Dep -> Store : steps 7+9 — write diagram.puml + runbook.md
  alt confirmed dialect is Bicep
    Dep -> Infra : step 8 — generate SECURE-BY-DEFAULT infra/main.bicep (+ modules)
  else confirmed dialect is Terraform
    Dep -> Infra : step 8 — generate SECURE-BY-DEFAULT infra/main.tf (+ modules)
  end
  Dep -> Dep : step 11 — HAND OFF to SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE
end

== SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE (RUN) ==
note over Dep
  Phase B. The runbook written in Phase A is the EXECUTION
  PLAN the skill now walks itself (steps 11-16).
end note
group step 12 — AUTH, managed by the skill (USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE)
  Dep -> CLI : az login (interactive device/browser)
  CLI --> Op : complete the auth handshake
  Op --> Dep : authenticated
  Dep -> CLI : az account set --subscription <target>
  opt wrong or ambiguous subscription
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING: surface the subscription mismatch; STOP
  end
end
group step 13 — PREFLIGHT dry-run before any apply (OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-DRYRUN-BEFORE-APPLY)
  Dep -> CLI : validate IaC (terraform validate / az bicep build)
  Dep -> CLI : DRY-RUN (terraform plan / az deployment what-if)
  CLI --> Dep : plan diff
  Dep -> Op : show the diff
end
group step 14 — EXECUTE, autonomous except irreversible; HALT on first error (OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-HALT-ON-ERROR)
  Dep -> CLI : resource group + ACR create; docker build + push (idempotent, AUTONOMOUS)
  Dep -> Op : BLOCKING confirm — APPLY this plan?\n(one gate covering infra apply + secret writes + migration job)
  Op --> Dep : approve (OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-PAUSE-IRREVERSIBLE)
  Dep -> CLI : apply infra (terraform apply / az deployment create)
  CLI -> Az : provision Container Apps, ACR, Postgres, Key Vault, OpenAI
  Dep -> CLI : provision secrets (az keyvault secret set)
  CLI -> Az : write secrets into Key Vault
  Dep -> CLI : run migration job (completes BEFORE traffic)
  CLI -> Az : schema migrate
  Dep -> CLI : deploy new revision at 0% traffic; health-check
  opt any step failed
    Dep -> Op : HALT — report the failing step; run NO further step
  end
end
group step 15 — GO-LIVE, never auto-confirmed (USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE / OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-GOLIVE-CONFIRMED)
  Dep -> Op : SURFACE full billing multi-factor gate state\n(ENABLE_PRODUCTION_BILLING, APP_ENV, DATABASE_MARKER,\nPUBLIC_HOST, APPLE_ENVIRONMENT, App Attest prod); BLOCKING confirm
  Op --> Dep : confirm go-live
  Dep -> CLI : route 100% traffic to the new revision (GO LIVE)
  CLI -> Az : live-traffic cutover
end
Dep -> CLI : step 16 — verify ingress responds + revision healthy
Dep --> Op : report — deployed and LIVE, or HALTED at the failing step

== SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT ==
Op -> Render : /mdd-render
Render -> Store : read .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml
Render -> Rendered : write .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg\n(deterministic mirror; additive, non-gating)
Render --> Op : rendered SVG list

note over Store
  .mdd/deploy/ is an inspection artifact only.
  /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the /mdd-cycle
  parity loop never read it.
end note
@enduml
